President Trump addressed a gathering of police chiefs and sheriffs, thanking them for their service and expressing his support for law enforcement. He highlighted his administration's efforts to reduce violent crime, including funding for the Project Safe Neighborhoods initiative and the prosecution of violent criminals. The President also emphasized the importance of border security in combating drug trafficking and criminal organizations. He praised the bravery and dedication of law enforcement officers and called for stronger border security measures, including the construction of a border wall. The President also addressed the issue of human trafficking and pledged to use all available resources to combat this problem. He recognized the heroism of law enforcement officers during natural disasters and terrorist attacks, and called for respect and support for law enforcement. The President concluded by expressing his gratitude to all law enforcement personnel and reaffirming his commitment to their safety and the safety of the American people.